        "title": "npm with java - throwing errors",
        "body": "<p>I need to install a java based package with NPM. I also can't do <code>npm install java<\/code> <\/p>\n\n<p>When I try to install said package, I get the following error:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>ld: warning: directory not found for option\n  '-L/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk-9.0.1.jdk/Contents/Home/jre/lib/server'\n  ld: library not found for -ljvm<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>What is <code>-ljvm<\/code>? I cannot find anything on google about this flag or on Stack Overflow.<\/p>\n\n<p>Has anyone else seen this error? How did they fix it?<\/p>\n\n<p>More details: I'm on MacOSX Sierra, java version 9.0.1, npm version 5.6.0 <\/p>\n",
